hopobject.body: I wrote about turning a Raspberry Pi into a completely mobile GPS streamer, so I felt like it was time to show the Beaglebone Black some love. I applied Adafruit’s Ultimate GPS Breakout Board to the BBB to try out using UART without the USB to TTL serial cable. There were two reasons for this: 1) I really wanted to try out the UART ports, and 2) the BBB only has one USB port and I didn’t want to waste it on a serial cable.....................
hopobject.shortdesc: Make your BeagleBone Black GPS mobile while streaming your location, speed, and altitude data.
